                    [drupal:path] =&gt; Array
                        (
                            [description] =&gt; Drupal: Drupal path like &quot;node/add/story&quot; or path alias with support for wildcards.&lt;br /&gt;

Query parameters are stripped off before the path gets examined. P.e. &quot;node/add/story?destination=node&quot; becomes &quot;node/add/story&quot; first. If you want to access query parameters have a look at property system:query_param provided by &lt;a href=&quot;http://drupal.org/project/themekey_properties&quot;&gt;ThemeKey Properties&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
Wildcard characters are &quot;#&quot; for numeric parts and &quot;%&quot; for all characters. To match conditions against a certain part, use an identifier with the wildcard. For example &quot;comment/reply/#xyz&quot; matches all paths with &quot;comment/reply&quot; and a numeric third argument. You can then specify conditions for every wildcard argument using the property &quot;drupal:path:wildcard&quot; and the identifier you choose (&quot;xyz&quot; in this example).&lt;br /&gt;

These are the possible wildcard replacements for foo/bar/42/test.html:&lt;pre&gt;
foo/bar/42/test.html
foo/bar/42/%
foo/bar/42
foo/bar/%/test.html
foo/bar/%/%
foo/bar/%
foo/bar/#/test.html
foo/bar/#/%
foo/bar/#
foo/bar
foo/%/42/test.html
foo/%/42/%
foo/%/42
foo/%/%/test.html
foo/%/%/%
foo/%/%
foo/%/#/test.html
foo/%/#/%
foo/%/#
foo/%
foo
%/bar/42/test.html
%/bar/42/%
%/bar/42
%/bar/%/test.html
%/bar/%/%
%/bar/%
%/bar/#/test.html
%/bar/#/%
%/bar/#
%/bar
%/%/42/test.html
%/%/42/%
%/%/42
%/%/%/test.html
%/%/%/%
%/%/%
%/%/#/test.html
%/%/#/%
%/%/#
%/%
%
&lt;/pre&gt;
                            [validator] =&gt; themekey_validator_drupal_path
                        )

See &lt;a href=&quot;/drupal6-local/?q=admin/content/types&quot;&gt;admin/content/types&lt;/a&gt; for your content types (use column &quot;Type&quot;). Drupal default types are &quot;page&quot; and &quot;story&quot;.
                            [validator] =&gt; themekey_validator_node_type
                        )

                    [node:uid] =&gt; Array
                        (
                            [description] =&gt; Node: User ID - The user id (uid) of the author of the node. The user id can be found in the URL of the users profile page, &quot;user/23&quot; or &quot;user/23/edit&quot; (23 = uid). See &lt;a href=&quot;/drupal6-local/?q=admin/user/user/list&quot;&gt;admin/user/user/list&lt;/a&gt; for your users.
                            [validator] =&gt; themekey_validator_ctype_digit
                        )

                        (
                            [description] =&gt; System: Cookie - Every single cookie and it&#039;s value if present will be formatted like &#039;COOKIE_NAME=COOKIE_VALUE&#039;

                            [page cache] =&gt; 0
                        )

                            [description] =&gt; System: &#039;HTTPS&#039; - Set to &#039;true&#039; value if the script was queried through the HTTPS protocol, otherwise &#039;false&#039;.

                            [page cache] =&gt; 1

                    [system:query_param] =&gt; Array
                        (
                            [description] =&gt; System: Query Parameter - Every single query parameter other than &#039;q&#039; and it&#039;s value if present. Note that values are url decoded. Example: &#039;?q=node&amp;foo=bar&amp;dummy&amp;filter=tid%3A27&#039; will cause three entries &#039;foo=bar&#039;, &#039;dummy&#039; and &#039;filter=tid:27&#039;. For &#039;q&#039; see property drupal:get_q.
                            [page cache] =&gt; 1
                        )

                    [system:query_string] =&gt; Array
                        (
                            [description] =&gt; System: Query String - Complete query string except parameter &#039;q&#039;. Example: &#039;?q=node&amp;foo=bar&amp;dummy&amp;filter=tid%3A27&#039; will result in &#039;foo=bar&amp;dummy&amp;filter=tid%3A27&#039;. For &#039;q&#039; see property drupal:get_q.
                            [page cache] =&gt; 1
                        )

                    [system:random] =&gt; Array
                        (
                            [description] =&gt; System: Random - A random value that could be &#039;0&#039; or 1&#039;.

                            [page cache] =&gt; 0
                        )

                    [system:referer] =&gt; Array
                        (
                            [description] =&gt; System: &#039;HTTP_REFERER&#039; - The address of the page (if any) which referred the user agent to the current page. This is set by the user agent. Not all user agents will set this, and some provide the ability to modify HTTP_REFERER as a feature. In short, it cannot really be trusted.
                            [page cache] =&gt; 0
                        )
